LG Electronics, a global leader in consumer electronics has unveiled a new TV that will recapture the excitement of football matches. LG Electronics has proved beyond reasonable doubt that a larger TV will always do the job of watching action played across giant fields better, by displaying zoomed-out footage in amazing details. LG  General Manager, Home Entertainment Division at LG Electronics West Africa, Vanjamin Kim noted: “OLED delivers the widest viewing angles in the game, the 88-inch LG Signature Oled 8k TV is the pinnacle of home spectating, while its smaller 48-inch sibling delivers the same wide viewing angle to smaller rooms and  LG Oled TV has continued to garner rave reviews for best-in-class uniformity.” said.